<TEXT>
officials of the world alpine ski 
championships maintained tuesday that no safety violations 
contributed to the death of a cousin of spains king but a champion 
skiier suggested the victim was on a closed course 
the duke of cadiz a 52yearold first cousin of king juan carlos 
and member of the international governing body of ski racing was 
killed monday at the beaver creek ski resort when he ran into a 
cable being raised to hold a finishline banner for the mens 
downhill course 
alfonso de borbon y de dampierre suffered neck lacerations and 
apparently died instantly eagle county coroner donna meineke said 
an official cause of death had not been released by tuesday 
afternoon 
de borbon was at onetime married to the granddaughter of spanish 
dictator francisco franco although he was not in the line of 
succession to the spanish throne he was a descendant of louis xiv 
the french sun king and was the bourbon or legitimist candidate 
for king had the monarchy ever been restored in france 
king juan carlos and queen sofia in spain expressed their sorrow 
over his death 
there is no reason to believe that any safety violations 
occurred bob knous president of the championships organizing 
committee told a news conference tuesday 
it truly appears that this was an accident a very very 
unfortunate and tragic incident knous said 
sheriff aj johnson would not say tuesday night whether eagle 
county officials agree with knous 
we will make no conclusions about safety violations not until 
the investigation is done johnson said i will discuss the 
investigation with the district attorney until then we are looking 
at all possibilities 
but defending world downhill champion peter mueller of 
switzerland said the victim and other ski officials ignored normal 
procedures when they skied down a closed course 
johnson who said his investigation would take a month confirmed 
that the course was closed but said we believe he de borbon 
had the authority to be on there 
de borbon was skiing monday with companions when he hit the cable 
as course workers were moving the finish line and banners uphill 
from the end of the slalom course to the end of the downhill 
witnesses said one of the companions former austrian olympic 
champion toni sailer saw the cable and warned de borbon who 
acknowledged the warning but still slammed into it at neck level 
according to johnson 
knous said there were no safety violations despite the fact that 
the course was closed following an inspection by the international 
ski federation known by its french initials as fis also there were 
no banners or identifying material on the cable that the duke hit 
he said he couldnt comment on whether the duke and his skiing 
companions should have been on the course at the time 
mueller 31 one of the favorites in saturdays race said 
normally when we prepare for a competition the course is closed 
but here the fis is skiing down for pleasure i think thats a big 
mistake if the downhill course is closed it should be closed for 
all people 
downhill training went on as scheduled tuesday although social 
events were canceled or postponed officials of the championships 
wore black armbands and flags throughout the ski resort flew at 
halfstaff 
the spanish ski team which had been training at another colorado 
ski resort still planned to come to vail and compete knous said 
the championship meet continues through this weekend 
de borbon served as spains ambassador to sweden from 1969 to 
1973 was president of the spanish skiing federation from 1977 to 
1984 and an eighttime spanish skiing champion 
de borbons father was the elder brother of king juan carlos 
father both mens fathers were the sons of king alfonso xiii who 
abdicated the spanish throne in 1931 
the duke married carmen franco in 1972 and they divorced in 1982 
in february 1984 the older of his two sons was killed in an auto 
accident in which de borbon was driving a judge ruled that de 
borbon had been negligent and stripped him of the custody of his 
other son 
francisco fernandezochoa the slalom gold medalist at the 1972 
olympics and a close friend of the duke said de borbon liked to 
ski fast and drive fast 
referring to the dukes divorce the fatal auto accident and the 
skiing tragedy fernandezochoa described the victim as an unlucky 
person bad things happened to him 
</TEXT>
