athens bus drivers are being sent to charm school 
the 43 million program is aimed at improving the image of the 
capitals public transportation system which faces stiff 
competition from taxis whose cost is among the cheapest in the world 
classes such as driver and communication with the public and 
english for drivers are part of the 15day courses for the staff 
of the semiprivate urban transportation company 
the classes will help the driver control his mediterranean 
temperament but passengers must also understand that its not 
the drivers fault when the bus is late said andreas kolas a 
spokesman for the union of bus drivers 
quarrels often break out between bus drivers and passengers irked 
by waiting for buses or when riders insist on getting off where 
there is no bus stop 
because of the chaotic state of public transportation bus 
routes and timetables are rarely available tourists often take 
taxis which cost about 2 for a threemile ride the bus fare is 20 
cents 
kolas said drivers manners arent helped by the aggravation of 
navigating the capitals notoriously congested streets 
according to the transit companys chairman vassilis xeomeritis 
about 3500 of the 5000 bus drivers are very experienced but 
older people with almost no education 
our drivers could use some retraining they must understand 
that passengers are our customers and that its the drivers duty to 
serve the public xenomeritis said 
the corporations 1200 buses cover the whole of athens a 
120squaremile area with only one subway line crossing the city 
more than 70 percent of athenians commute by bus daily 
