congress repealing the provision is now part of a package of 
legislation related to a pending 50 percent pay raise 
its an embarrassment to them norman ornstein a political 
analyst with the american enterprise institute said monday its 
the sort of question not too many members who were there before 1980 
want to have asked of them 
i think its a foregone conclusion that theyll do away with 
it 
more than 61 million in surplus campaign funds is sitting in the 
accounts of 191 house members and 71 senators who were in congress 
when the law was passed a grandfather clause in the law allows 
them to convert the money for personal use an action forbidden for 
those who came to congress later 
on the average house members who were grandfathered in hold 
