development 
pakistans nuclear intentions have been a source of friction in 
past relations with the united states although us policymakers 
sought to put those concerns aside in recent years because of 
pakistans cooperation in funneling weapons to the antisoviet 
rebels in neighboring afghanistan 
now that soviet troops are being withdrawn however the nuclear 
issue has come back to the forefront of relations between the two 
countries administration officials have said us aid to pakistan 
may be cut off after sept 30 because president bush will not be 
