joel steinberg was convicted of beating to death 
his illegally adopted daughter but jurors rejected a murder charge 
because his livein companion could have saved lisas life 
during nearly 12 hours she lay comatose on a bathroom floor 
eight days of heated deliberations ended monday when the jury 
reached the manslaughter verdict in the case that focused national 
attention on domestic violence and the question of who should report 
cases of suspected child abuse 
by acquitting steinberg of seconddegree murder the jurors 
decided that the disbarred lawyer had not shown depraved 
indifference to human life when he struck 6yearold lisa in a 
