the package according to leadership sources would 
end the honoraria system which has allowed rankandfile house 
members to keep up 26850 of the money they earn each year from 
speeches articles and other appearances 
abolition of the grandfather loophole in campaign financing 
law the loophole has allowed 190 house members who were in office 
as of jan 8 1980 to stockpile more than 39 million in surplus 
campaign money for their personal use the provision does not apply 
to senators 
restrict travel probably through time limits that is often 
paid for by special interests who invite lawmakers for speeches and 
plant tours this would prevent members from getting long vacations 
at resorts even if they speak for free 
restrict nonhonoraria income such as fees for serving on 
