<TEXT>
seasonal stirrings are about to lead the 
nations groundhogs from their snug burrows in search of lady 
groundhogs 
thats right when the furry mammals set forth in midwinter they 
couldnt care less about making weather predictions researchers say 
its hormones that get them moving only the timing proves a boon 
for small town chambers of commerce which seek publicity by taking 
advantage of the appearance of the animals and the associated 
ancient weather folklore 
feb 2 known as groundhog day in the united states has been a 
time for weather prognostications for centuries the date is also 
known as candlemas in the christian tradition a feast somewhat 
overshadowed by the commercial hype in recent years 
the popular idea of predicting winters end from animal behavior 
extends back at least to the ancient celts and was spread by the 
roman legions 
over the centuries farmers came to consider the celebration 
occurring about halfway between the winter solstice and the spring 
equinox a good time to try to make weather predictions applying 
the theory that the rest of winter would be the opposite of that on 
candlemas 
if candlemas be bright and clear therell be two winters in 
the year goes one traditional british rhyme if candlemas bring 
clouds and rain go winter and come not again 
similar beliefs are reported from ireland scotland france and 
spain so serious was this taken that some german farmers were said 
to have preferred to see a wolf in the stable than that candlemas 
day be pleasant and clear 
it was the germans who settled in pennsylvania who brought to 
america the tradition of predicting the weather on this date 
in europe they had looked to the first movements of hibernating 
bears hedgehogs and badgers for weather predictions on this side 
of the ocean the honor fell to the woodchuck also known as the 
groundhog or marmot 
woodchucks do begin to leave hibernation at this time of year 
at least in some parts of the nation but scientists report that 
whats on the animals minds is sex not weather 
the males come out of the burrows first while female groundhogs 
wont awaken for a week or more in the meantime the males search 
for food and fight among themselves according to researchers in 
maryland and pennsylvania 
the folk belief however is that animals somehow know future 
weather and if they end their hibernation and sally forth spring 
is close 
thus developed the worry that a shadow might frighten the animal 
back into its home leading to a prediction of six more weeks of 
winter 
most folks consider that bad news 
in the more northerly areas of the country however some people 
are said to hope that the groundhog will see its shadow predicting 
that winter will last only six more weeks 
the us naval observatory meanwhile relays a report that 
sailors who have been stationed at guantanamo bay say local people 
in cuba have a somewhat similar tradition 
that is that around this date banana rats find a tree to climb 
and relax in if they settle at a low level of the tree it will be a 
bad year for hurricanes while rats climbing high in the trees means 
a mild hurricane season the belief goes 
for the more religious the church observations on feb 2 are 
known as the feast of the presentation of the lord and the feast of 
the purification of mary 
this celebrates the time when mary as required by jewish law 
went to the temple in jerusalem to be purified 40 days after giving 
birth to a son and to present that son jesus to god 
that presentation of jesus said to bring light to the world 
helped lead to the custom of blessing on this date the candles 
destined to be used for the rest of the year hence the name 
candlemas 
and even those candles extend the weatherfolklore connection 
with the superstition that a candle blessed on this date will 
protect a home if lighted during a thunderstorm 
</TEXT>
