recovery which has lasted a peacetime record of six years will 
some day end in a new recession he said the imbalances that 
normally preceded a downturn were not now in evidence 
greenspan said that rather than pushing the economy into another 
downturn he believes the feds efforts to boost interest rates 
would extend the length of the recovery by keeping inflationary 
forces under control 
