a federal judge said tuesday he 
probably will allow the immigration and naturalization service to 
return to a policy of restricting political asylum applicants to 
southern texas pending reviews 
us district judge filemon vela extended until feb 20 an order 
blocking the procedure but added at that time unless im 
persuaded otherwise the restraining order will be lifted 
were pleased with the results said william joyce associate 
general counsel for the ins who traveled from washington for 
tuesdays hearing the judge was fair 
ins critics cited a sharp increase in homeless central americans 
