effect dec 16 a group of immigration attorneys sued the ins over 
the matter here on jan 6 and on jan 9 vela issued a temporary 
restraining order blocking the procedure 
under the procedure the district began requiring asylum 
applicants to file their claims in harlingen and await decisions 
there in 30 days a period in which they were not allowed to work 
the most visible effect of the travel restriction was a rugged 
campsite east of brownsville where more than 300 central americans 
camped out on the ground under discarded cardboard and sheets of 
plastic 
huge case backlogs in cities such as miami and los angeles made 
it necessary to keep the immigrants near their points of entry while 
