<TEXT>
wind damage to land in the great plains is up 
sharply reflecting the 1988 drought that hit much of the nation in 
the spring and summer the agriculture department said tuesday 
wilson scaling chief of the departments soil conservation 
service said nearly 22 million acres were reported damaged in 
november and december up more than 80 percent from 12 million 
acres in the same two months of 1987 
a lot of the damage is a result of drought scaling said 
the reasons vary by area but major factors are lack of crop 
residue and poor vegetative cover both caused by a lack of 
moisture 
scaling said more than 80 percent of the land reported damaged 
was cropland the remainder primarily rangeland 
texas accounted for more than 30 percent of the erosion damage in 
november and december with 664128 acres 
scaling said that in addition to the damaged land in november and 
december nearly 19 million acres were in condition to blow 
with five months still remaining in the critical wind season 
november and december are the first two months of an annual 
sevenmonth season when winds are highest and the soils are driest 
in the great plains surveys were made in 541 counties of the 
10state region 
although the 198788 season began with relatively light damage 
it picked up as moisture conditions worsened when the season ended 
last may 31 more than 13 million acres had been damaged the 
secondlargest acreage since the agency began records in 1935 
the most widespread was in 1955 when about 16 million acres of 
great plains land were damaged by wind another bad year was 198081 
when 125 million acres were damaged 
according to the survey the statebystate breakdown comparing 
damaged acres in november and december with the damage during the 
same two months of 198788 included 
colorado 28795 acres damaged this season and 17070 in 198788 
kansas 135550 and 31520 
montana 510875 and 304023 
nebraska 54405 and 74590 
new mexico 51100 and 3300 
north dakota 188200 and 230000 
oklahoma 68480 and 31288 
south dakota 112250 and 69400 
texas 664128 and 250220 
wyoming 346754 and 190885 
