<TEXT>
the billionaire bass brothers are often 
described as classic passive investors but their business ventures 
have kept them among the nations 400 richest people 
the bass dynasty traces its roots to the forays of wildcatter sid 
richardson who made a series of successful oil strikes in west 
texas upon his death in 1959 he willed most of his money to his 
partner and nephew perry bass 
after vastly expanding richardsons holdings perry retired in 
the late 1960s and left the family empire to his four sons who each 
inherited 28 million they combined assets to form bass brothers 
enterprises which was managed by eldest son sid bass 
with bold moves from the oil patch into stocks and real estate 
the brothers added to their collective and individual fortunes 
among their most lucrative ventures the basses netted an 850 
million capital gain after helping to thwart a 1985 takeover fight 
for walt disney co also that year the family liquidated bass 
brothers enterprises its primary investment vehicle and divided 
the assets four ways freeing the brothers to cut some individual 
deals 
since then robert bass has focused much of his energy on the 
information sector in 1985 he led a group that made a 205 million 
investment in cincinnatibased taft broadcasting co that was worth 
718 million two years later he and two other shareholders divided 
tafts assets with the bass group getting 1575 million in cash a 
television station in columbus ohio and two large cable television 
properties 
in 1988 robert bass was instrumental in prying away the westin 
hotel chain from allegis corp for 153 billion in march he sold 
the plaza hotel in manhattan to fellow billionaire donald j trump 
for 410 million 
last may 17 he reached an agreement to purchase bell amp howell 
co a publishing information services company in skokie ill 
on the same day a group that he led proposed to buy macmillan 
inc the move put the publishing giant in play and it was acquired 
last fall by british publisher robert maxwell for 25 billion and 
gave the bass group a gain of about 75 million on its holdings 
before expenses 
most recently the bass group put up 350 million for the bailout 
of insolvent american savings and loan association of california a 
subsidiary of financial corp of america 
the brothers zealously guard their privacy persistently refusing 
interviews and shunning transactions that would require much 
financial disclosure 
they have been described as atypical texas tycoons with their 
conservative style and reserved manner in fort worth they are 
universally revered for their civic investments 
sid is director of the generous sid richardson foundation ed 
often described as the family maverick has been more interested in 
arts and environmental projects lee is working with sid while 
robert has taken an interest in some political projects 
the big difference in the basses and most people like the 
basses is that theyre really not looking for any credit for what 
they do they do it because they think its what they should do and 
whats good said dee kelly a fort worth lawyer and longtime 
family friend 
despite their financial muscle the basses arent the 
strongarming type preferring to work with the management of target 
companies as they did in the disney situation checchi noted 
