us district judge mary johnson lowe declared a mistrial in that 
proceeding jan 10 because of an error by lowenson who failed to 
reveal a report that concluded a key piece of evidence had been 
altered 
the second trial was convened after us supreme court justice 
thurgood marshall refused to continue a delay requested by the 
defense which claimed a second trial would violate the defendants 
right to avoid double jeopardy 
