outstanding stock under pennsylvania law a special meeting must be 
called if one is requested by the holders of at least 20 percent of 
a companys outstanding voting stock 
state law requires the company to call the meeting within two 
months of the request centaur said 
pennwalt officials said they were in the process of reviewing 
the demands to determine whether they have been submitted by the 
requisite shareholders and whether they are in a form that would be 
effective 
